OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F405A1773230584
OL,3,CClimbing on Holocaust Memorial Garden
OL,4,Cto become a crime ` Lords
OL,6,FClimbing on the statue of wartime
OL,7,Fprime minister Sir Winston Churchill
OL,8,Foutside the Houses of Parliament,
OL,9,Fwhich was last month daubed with the
OL,10,Fwords "Free Palestine" and "Never
OL,11,FAgain is Now", would also become a
OL,12,Fcrime.
OL,14,FBuilt in 1983, the Holocaust Memorial
OL,15,FGarden stone is marked with the words:
OL,16,F"For these I weep. Streams of tears
OL,17,Fflow from my eyes because of the
OL,18,Fdestruction of my people."
OL,26,@rD@GOUrD@VO]rD@\OUsD@MO]xD@AOUzD@ZO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/10
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,406,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F405A1773230584
OL,3,CClimbing on Holocaust Memorial Garden
OL,4,Cto become a crime ` Lords
OL,6,FLord Parkinson of Whitley Bay, who
OL,7,Fproposed including the Holocaust
OL,8,FMemorial Garden in the Bill, said that
OL,9,F"sadly, that had to be covered in
OL,10,Ftarpaulin as recently as April 2024",
OL,11,Fpointing to a fear it could have been
OL,12,Fvandalised in an antisemitic attack.
OL,14,FSeveral newspapers at the time
OL,15,Fpublished a picture of the boulder
OL,16,Fcovered by a blue tarpaulin.
OL,18,FLord Parkinson, a Conservative peer,
OL,19,Fsaid "many other memorials" were
OL,20,Fworthy of additional protection from
OL,21,Fclimbing.
OL,26,@qD@AOUrD@dO]{D@FOU{D@[O]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/10
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
